abstract: >
  Darwin Scaffold Studio is an open-source Julia platform for analyzing tissue
  engineering scaffolds from MicroCT and SEM imaging data. Features include:
  porosity measurement (<1% error), pore size analysis (14% APE vs manual
  ground truth), interconnectivity and tortuosity computation, TPMS scaffold
  generation for validation, and integration with OBO Foundry biomedical
  ontologies. Validated against PoreScript dataset (DOI: 10.5281/zenodo.5562953).

